[Amit Varma]: But then, you know, you got to do what you got to do.

02:30:14.080 --> 02:30:19.920
[Amit Varma]: You know, if if one stops oneself from saying what, you know, then then why say anything

02:30:19.920 --> 02:30:20.920
[Amit Varma]: at all?

02:30:20.920 --> 02:30:22.880
[Amit Varma]: It kind of comes down to that.

02:30:22.880 --> 02:30:27.840
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, something interesting that you kind of said about, you know, the marriage

02:30:27.840 --> 02:30:31.240
[Amit Varma]: years, the whole spousal thing that after a while you kind of know each other because

02:30:31.240 --> 02:30:32.240
[Unknown]: everything is done.

02:30:32.240 --> 02:30:36.760
[Amit Varma]: And that reminded me of this beautiful poem by my favorite poet Mark Strand, which I'll

02:30:36.760 --> 02:30:37.760
[Amit Varma]: read out.

02:30:37.760 --> 02:30:38.760
[Amit Varma]: It's a prose poem.

02:30:38.760 --> 02:30:42.320
[Amit Varma]: So it's called Harmony in the Boudoir by Mark Strand.

02:30:42.320 --> 02:30:45.520
[Amit Varma]: After years of marriage, he stands at the foot of the bed and tells his wife that she

02:30:45.520 --> 02:30:49.760
[Amit Varma]: will never know him, that for everything he says, there is more that he does not say,

02:30:49.760 --> 02:30:54.440
[Amit Varma]: that behind each word he utters there is another word and hundreds more behind that one.

02:30:54.440 --> 02:30:59.240
[Amit Varma]: All those unsaid words, he says, contain his true self, which has been betrayed by the

02:30:59.240 --> 02:31:01.240
[Amit Varma]: superficial self before her.

02:31:01.240 --> 02:31:05.440
[Amit Varma]: So you see, he says, kicking off his slippers, I am more than what I have led you to believe

02:31:05.440 --> 02:31:06.440
[Amit Varma]: I am.

02:31:06.440 --> 02:31:08.040
[Amit Varma]: Oh, you silly man, says his wife.

02:31:08.040 --> 02:31:09.040
[Amit Varma]: Of course you are.

02:31:09.040 --> 02:31:14.200
[Amit Varma]: I find it just thinking of you having so many cells receding into nothingness is very exciting

02:31:14.200 --> 02:31:16.480
[Amit Varma]: that you barely exist as you are.

02:31:16.480 --> 02:31:17.480
[Amit Varma]: Couldn't please me more.

02:31:17.480 --> 02:31:18.480
[Amit Varma]: It's not good.

02:31:18.480 --> 02:31:19.480
[Amit Varma]: I kind of love this.

02:31:19.480 --> 02:31:23.120
[Amit Varma]: And this also leads me to the question is that how much of ourselves, what we think

02:31:23.120 --> 02:31:25.680
[Amit Varma]: we are, is constructed for ourselves?

02:31:25.680 --> 02:31:27.720
[Amit Varma]: Like, is that something that you think about?

02:31:27.720 --> 02:31:30.360
[Amit Varma]: Do you sometimes think that that I'm just being dishonest?

02:31:30.360 --> 02:31:33.560
[Amit Varma]: I'm just putting a face out there that I don't know if there's a real me.

02:31:33.560 --> 02:31:37.680
[Amit Varma]: I mean, I don't know if anyone has a real me in that sense, that the self is always

02:31:37.680 --> 02:31:42.560
[Amit Varma]: a sort of a construction and for others and oneself, if that makes any sense to you.

02:31:42.560 --> 02:31:49.520
[Guest]: So one of the things, I've never mustered up the courage to do this and probably won't.

02:31:49.520 --> 02:32:01.680
[Guest]: But they say that if you do acid or mushrooms, psilocybin mushrooms, these are chemicals

02:32:01.680 --> 02:32:06.840
[Guest]: that dissolve your sense of self and transform you as a person.

02:32:06.840 --> 02:32:14.760
[Guest]: So the self is a really it's a construct and like almost all of mystical philosophy is,

02:32:14.760 --> 02:32:18.680
[Guest]: you know, is about that and about how to see the world.

02:32:18.680 --> 02:32:21.440
[Guest]: So I've struggled with this.

02:32:21.440 --> 02:32:23.720
[Guest]: I've had spiritual insights.

02:32:23.720 --> 02:32:30.360
[Guest]: I used to do this thing where I used to sit in front of a mirror and stare at myself.

02:32:30.360 --> 02:32:34.040
[Guest]: And if you do this long enough, you just stare at yourself.

02:32:34.040 --> 02:32:35.040
[Guest]: Just don't close your eyes.

02:32:35.040 --> 02:32:36.040
[Guest]: Do nothing.

02:32:36.040 --> 02:32:37.040
[Guest]: Just sit.

02:32:37.040 --> 02:32:40.800
[Guest]: Ideally, sit in front of keep a mirror, preferably a full length mirror.

02:32:40.800 --> 02:32:42.800
[Guest]: Just keep staring at yourself.

02:32:42.800 --> 02:32:49.680
[Guest]: And after some time, you'll suddenly have this thing, you know, it's very fleeting.

02:32:49.680 --> 02:32:51.440
[Guest]: It'll come and it'll go.

02:32:51.440 --> 02:32:55.480
[Guest]: But for that fleeting moment, it will be, is it really me?

02:32:55.480 --> 02:32:56.480
[Guest]: You know, what am I?

02:32:56.480 --> 02:32:57.480
[Guest]: Who am I?

02:32:57.480 --> 02:32:59.000
[Guest]: Kind of thing.

02:32:59.000 --> 02:33:06.400
[Guest]: And unfortunately, it is nowhere as transformative as they say acid or those mushrooms are.

02:33:06.400 --> 02:33:16.200
[Guest]: But it's true that these constructs that we make for ourselves define everything that

02:33:16.200 --> 02:33:23.360
[Guest]: I personally believe that what we are trying to do, all of us, is we are trying to be internally

02:33:23.360 --> 02:33:25.200
[Guest]: consistent is what I think.

02:33:25.200 --> 02:33:31.640
[Guest]: So we, even people who have just absolutely the most absurd, untrue, even people like

02:33:31.640 --> 02:33:38.320
[Guest]: Donald Trump, somewhere internally, they have some consistent image of it.

02:33:38.320 --> 02:33:44.520
[Guest]: And they hang on to it because if that breaks, everything is gone for them.

02:33:44.520 --> 02:33:51.280
[Guest]: But for most of us, it's probably desirable that it breaks and you start seeing things

02:33:51.280 --> 02:33:54.000
[Guest]: as they are or as they are from other.

02:33:54.000 --> 02:33:56.920
[Guest]: I haven't, I haven't really succeeded in doing any of this.

02:33:56.920 --> 02:33:58.160
[Guest]: I've tried.

02:33:58.160 --> 02:34:00.800
[Guest]: I don't have the slightest idea how to go about it.

02:34:00.800 --> 02:34:05.280
[Guest]: I don't know if you had any experiences or experiments in this direction.

02:34:05.280 --> 02:34:06.640
[Amit Varma]: No, not at all.

02:34:06.640 --> 02:34:11.480
[Amit Varma]: I mean, Sam Harris keeps talking about meditation and psychedelic drugs, how they both get you

02:34:11.480 --> 02:34:12.760
[Amit Varma]: past the sense of the self.

02:34:12.760 --> 02:34:16.640
[Amit Varma]: And obviously, the whole idea of meditation is that it can take you kind of above yourself

02:34:16.640 --> 02:34:20.520
[Amit Varma]: to a meta level where you can view yourself doing the things you do and thinking the things

02:34:20.520 --> 02:34:24.800
[Amit Varma]: you think and realizing that this is also a narrative, that, you know, on Twitter you

02:34:24.800 --> 02:34:29.480
[Amit Varma]: posture for others, but over here, you're also posturing for yourself.

02:34:29.480 --> 02:34:33.160
[Amit Varma]: And that's an interesting and kind of scary realization.

02:34:33.160 --> 02:34:38.880
[Amit Varma]: I once did go for this Vipashyana camp when I was very young in my 20s.

02:34:38.880 --> 02:34:43.560
[Amit Varma]: And so, you know, you got to stay silent for all those 10 days or whatever it is.

02:34:43.560 --> 02:34:50.240
[Amit Varma]: And it was horrible in the sense that it was horrible with one food related, you know,

02:34:50.240 --> 02:34:51.480
[Amit Varma]: good feeling at the end of it.

02:34:51.480 --> 02:34:56.720
[Amit Varma]: But it was horrible because after day two, my head was just full of sexual fantasies.

02:34:56.720 --> 02:35:03.600
[Amit Varma]: So I was observing myself having sexual fantasies and for days that is just terrible.

02:35:03.600 --> 02:35:04.600
[Guest]: It was nonsense.

02:35:04.600 --> 02:35:07.480
[Guest]: Have you ever tried mindfulness meditation?

02:35:07.480 --> 02:35:08.880
[Amit Varma]: I have since tried it.

02:35:08.880 --> 02:35:14.720
[Amit Varma]: But the point is that I haven't been mindful enough while trying it.

02:35:14.720 --> 02:35:15.720
[Guest]: I same with me.

02:35:15.720 --> 02:35:16.720
[Guest]: I haven't been.

