[Amit Varma]: After that, we went to an Italian restaurant, I remember for a meal after we kind of got

02:35:54.440 --> 02:35:56.880
[Amit Varma]: back from Igatpuri where it was.

02:35:56.880 --> 02:35:58.840
[Amit Varma]: And it was a spectacular meal.

02:35:58.840 --> 02:36:03.760
[Amit Varma]: And it was a spectacular meal, not because it was a spectacular meal, but because I could

02:36:03.760 --> 02:36:10.240
[Amit Varma]: taste every little nuance of that, like every little nuance of that I could taste.

02:36:10.240 --> 02:36:16.200
[Amit Varma]: My senses were so acute, and I was like, ki haan yaar, aise khana chahiye.

02:36:16.200 --> 02:36:19.080
[Amit Varma]: But then you're, you know, back to normal by the next meal, and you don't even know

02:36:19.080 --> 02:36:22.920
[Amit Varma]: what you ate by the end of it, you know, chicken khaya, mutton khaya, and you finish the food

02:36:22.920 --> 02:36:23.920
[Guest]: and you're like.

